The Warren Buffett Way, a book by author Robert Hagstrom, outlines the principles of value investing practiced by successful investor Warren Buffett.The first edition, published in 1994, sold over a million copies and spent 21 weeks on the New York Times Hardcover Nonfiction Best Seller list. A decade later, Hagstrom issued a second, expanded edition.The principles included:Purchase businesses with excellent long-term prospectsPurchase businesses at a large discount to their intrinsic valuePurchase businesses with a high return on invested capitalPurchase businesses with honest managers↑ ↑